  "prompt": "How can I get good marks in RTU exam even if I dont know any answer of question paper?",
  "response": "Getting good marks in an exam when you don't know the answers can be challenging, but here are some strategies you can consider:\n\n1. **Attempt All Questions**: Even if you are unsure of the answers, attempt every question as best as you can. Sometimes partial credit is awarded for making a valid attempt or for partially correct responses.\n\n2. **Eliminate Wrong Choices**: If the exams have multiple-choice questions, try to eliminate the clearly wrong options first. This increases the chances of guessing the correct answer.\n\n3. **Stay Calm and Positive**: Stress can hinder your ability to think clearly. Stay calm and maintain a positive attitude throughout the exam.\n\n4. **Use Logic and Common Sense**: Try to reason out the answer using logic and common sense. Even if you don\u2019t know the specific answer, you might be able to make an educated guess.\n\n5. **Write Clearly and Neatly**: Ensure that your handwriting is legible and your answers are well-organized. Sometimes, presentation can make a difference in how your answer is perceived.\n\n6. **Review the Entire Paper First**: Scan through the entire paper quickly at the beginning to identify questions you might have some idea about. Answer these questions first to maximize your score.\n\n7. **Focus on Keywords**: Sometimes the question may contain keywords that hint at the required answer. Pay attention to these clues.\n\n8. **Show Work**: In subjects like mathematics, show every step of your work. Even if the end result is not correct, you might get partial marks for the correct method.\n\n9. **Time Management**: Allocate your time wisely. Spend appropriate time on each question, and don\u2019t spend too long on questions you don\u2019t know.\n\n10. **Revise Broad Topics**: For future exams, try to gain at least a basic understanding of broad topics. This will help you make educated guesses and provide more complete answers.\n\n11. **Study Smart**: Use study guides, attend review sessions, and participate in group studies to improve your overall knowledge.\n\nRemember, preparation is the best strategy for success in exams. Try to study effectively and consistently in the future to reduce instances where you face questions you cannot answer.",
